    %h4 Cookies

    %ol
      %li Tueetion may store some information (commonly known as a "cookie") on your computer when you log in to Tueetion’s Digital Assets. Tueetion’s Digital Assets is able to read these cookies for information purposes when you revisit Tueetion’s Digital Assets. The type of information Tueetion collects as a result of a cookie being accepted by you is specific to your personal computer and includes the internet protocol (IP) address, the date and time the personal computer visited the Website, what parts of Tueetion’s Digital Assets were looked at and whether the web pages requested were delivered successfully. This information is anonymous; it represents a computer rather than a person.
      %li Tueetion uses the cookie information to improve its knowledge of the use of Tueetion’s Digital Assets and to enable Tueetion to be able to ascertain whether Tueetion’s Digital Assets are operating at an optimal level. This allows Tueetion to enhance its offerings to you and to provide an enjoyable and an innovative online experience.
      %li Some of Tueetion’s business partners may use cookies on Tueetion’s Digital Assets (for example, links to business partners). Tueetion does not want its business partners to use cookies to track Tueetion’s Digital Assets’ users' activities once they leave Tueetion’s Digital Assets. However, Tueetion may not have total control over how its business partners may use cookies on Tueetion’s Digital Assets. If you become aware that Tueetion’s business partner is placing an unwanted cookie on your hard drive, please contact Tueetion to assist Tueetion in resolving the problem.

    %h4 Data Retention

    %ol
      %li Your Personal Data can be retained until three (3) months from the date you notify Tueetion of your wish to limit or refrain from using your personal information, and may be retained in either a physical or electronic format. Upon the expiry of the aforementioned period, your personal data shall be securely and permanently deleted from Tueetion’s database.

    %h4 Security

    %ol
      %li Security measures, including Secure Socket Layer (SSL) encryption technology, are in place in order to protect personal information that Tueetion collects from unauthorised access, improper use or disclosure, unauthorised modification, unlawful destruction or accidental loss. The said personal information will be stored and backed up securely in an environmentally-controlled location. Only authorized people with user ID and password from Tueetion have access to the information. All Tueetion’s employees and data processors, who have access to and are associated with the processing of personal information, are obliged to respect the confidentiality of your account information.

    %h4 Changes to this Privacy Policy

    %ol
      %li From time to time, Tueetion may make changes to this Privacy Policy. If Tueetion makes any substantial changes to this Privacy Policy and the way in which it uses your personal data Tueetion will post these changes on this page. Please check this Privacy Policy on a regular basis. If this Privacy Policy changes in any way, it will be updated on this page. Regularly reviewing this page ensures you are updated on the information which is collected, how it is used and under what circumstances, if any, it is shared with other parties.

